Subject: [PATCH] newlib: restore _DEFUN/_AND/_NOARGS/_VOID in <_ansi.h>

libgloss/libsysbase (the newlib side of PSL1GHT's _r syscall
dispatchers) and PSL1GHT's own ppu/librt both still use the K&R-vs-
ANSI compatibility macros _DEFUN, _AND, _NOARGS, and _VOID.  Those
macros lived in newlib's <_ansi.h> through newlib 3.x and were
dropped in 4.x on the theory that the K&R compiler path is dead.

Modernizing every call site would touch ~75 files across libgloss
and PSL1GHT librt; the PSL1GHT v3 RFC already plans a naming pass
on top of that code.  Restore the macros in newlib's own <_ansi.h>
so both libgloss/libsysbase and PSL1GHT's librt compile cleanly
without carrying a separate shim header.

This supersedes the PSL1GHT-side _ansi.h interposition in
patches/psl1ght/0004 for the libgloss case; the PSL1GHT shim stays
in place because it interposes on PSL1GHT's own include path
(newlib is pulled via #include_next), and would in any case be
harmless even after this newlib patch lands.

diff --git a/newlib/libc/include/_ansi.h b/newlib/libc/include/_ansi.h
--- a/newlib/libc/include/_ansi.h
+++ b/newlib/libc/include/_ansi.h
@@ -79,4 +79,17 @@
 #define _NOINLINE_STATIC
 #endif

+/* PS3 toolchain: restore K&R-vs-ANSI compat macros newlib dropped in 4.x.
+   libgloss/libsysbase and PSL1GHT's librt both still use these.  Harmless
+   for any other consumer — they fall through #ifndef guards. */
+#ifndef _DEFUN
+# define _DEFUN(name, args, parms) name(parms)
+# define _AND   ,
+# define _NOARGS void
+#endif
+
+#ifndef _VOID
+# define _VOID void
+#endif
+
 #endif /* _ANSIDECL_H_ */
